Account config:

--> git config --global user.name "Your Name"
--> git config --global user.email "your_email@example.com"
--> git config list # checking for user configuration details 

--> git status # to check the files or folder status
--> git log # we can check the how many commits are done by the users updating the code.
--> git add . # move all files from working area to staging area ( files are in green colour after applying the git add . command before that the files are red colour)
--> git commit -m " comment " # move all files from staging area to git repository ( no colour in files)

--> git Branch Development # to create the Development Branch
--> git checkout Development # to moving the current branch to Development

--> git checkout -b Thanvish_web_application # it will create a branch and it will move to that new branch (Thanvish_web_application) ( here we can do point 12 and 13 at same time)

--> git merge Development   # to merge the files from Development to master if we are in master branch. 

--> git branch -D Development # to delete Development branch. 

--> git show head example # is used for cheking the example file data. 
--> git push # we can not directly push the file to the repository first
we have to add the repository to the branch below is the command
-- > git remote add origin https://github.com/rchappidi1/Thanvish_branch.git

--> git push origin master # to upload the files to the git branch repository.

--> git reflog # we can easily identify the head for the commit. example : We deleted the some branches in git so we have to recovery those data from the branch
1st we have to find the last commit in that branch and based on that we have to apply the get reflog and then identify that HEAD*{} then use the below command
-->git checkout -b Thanvish_web_application HEAD{1} : here -b will create the new branch based on the deleted one and HEAD{0} will identify the last commit and retrive the data.

